1
00:00:07,507 --> 00:00:09,384
-[water gurgling]
-[tracker beeping]

2
00:00:09,968 --> 00:00:12,679
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

3
00:00:34,910 --> 00:00:39,540
EP12: The Confession

4
00:00:55,597 --> 00:00:56,932
[deep exhale]

5
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:06,275
[Giho] Seriously, Do.

6
00:01:06,358 --> 00:01:08,068
I think we need to call 911 now.

7
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:11,029
I… I'm worried
something went wrong down there.

8
00:01:11,613 --> 00:01:13,782
What do you think we should do? Huh?

9
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:15,117
Just stay calm, okay?

10
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:19,538
[drone whirring]

11
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:22,958
What are you…

12
00:01:24,334 --> 00:01:27,045
[♪ tense music playing]

13
00:01:28,547 --> 00:01:30,716
[water gurgling]

14
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:40,809
[clunking]

15
00:01:40,892 --> 00:01:41,935
[Soryong grunts]

16
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:45,897
[Soryong groaning, panting]

17
00:01:50,777 --> 00:01:52,029
[gasping, grunting]

18
00:02:00,370 --> 00:02:01,580
It's here, Do!

19
00:02:01,663 --> 00:02:03,332
There it is. It's up!

20
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:04,875
[Giho] You see it?

21
00:02:08,420 --> 00:02:09,921
[♪ tense music continues]

22
00:02:10,881 --> 00:02:13,592
[panicked breathing]

23
00:02:20,891 --> 00:02:23,101
[breathing stops]

24
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:40,661
Soryong, come on.

25
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,288
[Han Do] Soryong!

26
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:47,834
Soryong!

27
00:02:48,877 --> 00:02:50,587
[screams] Soryong!

28
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:53,423
[♪ somber music playing]

29
00:02:57,803 --> 00:02:59,346
-[worried panting]
-[Giho] Ms. Oh!

30
00:03:00,222 --> 00:03:01,306
[timer beeping]

31
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:02,891
[gasps softly]

32
00:03:04,434 --> 00:03:06,728
[Giho] Where are you going?
No! Do! Don't do it!

33
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:08,647
-[Giho] Do!
-She needs our help!

34
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,691
-Han Do!
-Come on, Giho!

35
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:14,361
[screams] Oh Soryong!

36
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:18,073
[panting]

37
00:03:19,074 --> 00:03:21,493
[♪ somber music continues]

38
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:33,213
[♪ uplifting music playing]

39
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:34,923
[gasps]

40
00:03:37,134 --> 00:03:39,052
Oh! Hey, Ms. Oh!

41
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:41,471
[Giho] Ms. Oh! You're alive!

42
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:45,100
Hey! Come back!

43
00:03:45,183 --> 00:03:46,518
Ms. Oh!

44
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:47,853
[Giho] Over here! Over here!

45
00:03:47,936 --> 00:03:49,813
-[gasping]
-Holy shit, Ms. Oh!

46
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:51,648
[Giho cheering]

47
00:03:52,816 --> 00:03:54,234
Right here!

48
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:55,944
Yeah!

49
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:58,947
-[Giho] You don't see me? Whoa!
-[sobbing]

50
00:03:59,739 --> 00:04:00,782
[Giho] Over here!

51
00:04:00,866 --> 00:04:02,284
[Giho cheering]

52
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:03,702
Ms. Oh!

53
00:04:03,785 --> 00:04:06,037
Let's get out of there! Ms. Oh!

54
00:04:06,538 --> 00:04:07,664
[Giho cheering]

55
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:09,458
Do, c'mon, pool's closed!

56
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:13,086
Got it! I'm on my way right now.

57
00:04:15,714 --> 00:04:16,715
[gasps]

58
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:18,675
"From: Oh Soryong, Trigger"

59
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:20,302
You're telling me

60
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:22,554
Cho Jinman buys underage girls online,

61
00:04:22,637 --> 00:04:24,431
he murders them and then…

62
00:04:24,514 --> 00:04:25,515
dumps them in the reservoir?

63
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:27,559
I think, given our findings,

64
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:32,272
Virgin Slave is a website that sells
underage girls to its VIP clients.

65
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:34,524
And the assemblyman
was looking at their "products,"

66
00:04:34,608 --> 00:04:36,026
which can only be viewed by members.

67
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:37,652
So, open-and-shut case.

68
00:04:37,736 --> 00:04:39,362
[Ms. Hong] Might as well smuggle them
in Hanju's shipments.

69
00:04:39,446 --> 00:04:41,031
-Easy to hide.
-[sighs]

70
00:04:42,073 --> 00:04:45,243
And these bastards
own our nation's top newspaper?

71
00:04:45,327 --> 00:04:46,787
What a sick joke. Jesus…

72
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:49,998
I mean, this is enough for
an arrest warrant, at the very least.

73
00:04:50,081 --> 00:04:51,208
Don't you think?

74
00:04:52,209 --> 00:04:55,962
I don't know. Should we wait and stand by
while they run the tests to be safe?

75
00:04:56,046 --> 00:04:57,923
I just can't understand.

76
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:03,303
How messed up does the Hanju family
have to be for them to…

77
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:05,138
[deep inhale]

78
00:05:05,222 --> 00:05:07,265
I mean, this is worse than
anything we'd imagined.

79
00:05:07,349 --> 00:05:08,892
[Giho] Exactly.

80
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:11,561
Soryong, you okay there?

81
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:15,106
[sighs] Ah, seriously, man.

82
00:05:15,190 --> 00:05:17,317
We've been waiting over three hours.
What's taking so long?

83
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:21,696
[sighs in relief]

84
00:05:22,531 --> 00:05:23,532
Loony Han.

85
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:26,034
You were rude earlier.

86
00:05:26,618 --> 00:05:27,911
Huh?

87
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:29,830
"Oh Soryong!" What was that?

88
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:33,542
What was I supposed to say,
"Ms. Oh" or something?

89
00:05:34,626 --> 00:05:37,838
Could've tried "Ms. Oh."
Would've been shorter to say, at least.

90
00:05:37,921 --> 00:05:38,922
[scoffs]

91
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:41,550
Wow, someone's in a good mood. Huh?

92
00:05:41,633 --> 00:05:43,301
Why were you down there for so long?

93
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:48,849
I thought I was a goner.

94
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:53,144
I guess I passed out cold.

95
00:05:53,228 --> 00:05:54,980
[♪ gentle music playing]

96
00:05:55,564 --> 00:05:57,440
[Soryong's mom] Sweetie.

97
00:05:59,484 --> 00:06:01,361
Soryong.

98
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:04,197
[Han Do screaming] Oh Soryong!

99
00:06:06,491 --> 00:06:07,868
[Soryong] But then I heard you…

100
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:12,497
I heard you calling my name.

101
00:06:12,581 --> 00:06:13,957
[loud creaking, snapping]

102
00:06:20,505 --> 00:06:22,382
[♪ gentle music continues]

103
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:31,850
My mom had this big scar on her ankle.

104
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:34,644
Wait. Why are you telling us this?

105
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:37,647
When I was a little girl…

106
00:06:39,566 --> 00:06:42,319
she scolded me
and I ran and hid in an alley.

107
00:06:45,989 --> 00:06:48,283
My mom tried so hard to find me.

108
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:51,536
But I stayed put in that alleyway.

109
00:06:54,497 --> 00:06:57,459
I stayed put even when I saw her trip
and cut her ankle.

110
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:04,674
When I went to see my mom's body
after she died…

111
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:07,552
I saw the scar

112
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:10,764
on her ankle where it always was.

113
00:07:14,351 --> 00:07:15,477
[sighs]

114
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:24,152
I hate the burden of guilt.

115
00:07:27,030 --> 00:07:28,073
That's why I do this.

116
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:32,535
I hate when people ask,

117
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:36,623
"Why are you so obsessed
with the Cha Seongwook case?"

118
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:41,086
[Soryong] It's 'cause I knew
if I ignored it,

119
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:44,464
the guilt would eat away at me forever.

120
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:50,720
I did suspect that…

121
00:07:50,804 --> 00:07:53,098
digging deeper might reveal something.

122
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:55,225
Something huge.

123
00:07:57,602 --> 00:07:58,728
[scoffs]

124
00:08:02,732 --> 00:08:04,567
[Soryong sighs]
I never would've imagined…

125
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:07,028
we find this down there.

126
00:08:08,863 --> 00:08:11,282
[car approaching]

127
00:08:11,366 --> 00:08:12,492
Ms. Oh, look.

128
00:08:13,535 --> 00:08:14,786
-[Giho] What do we do?
-[car honking]

129
00:08:14,869 --> 00:08:17,122
-[Giho] What are we gonna do?
-Until the cops get here,

130
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:19,207
we have to do what we can
to protect the crime scene.

131
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:21,710
[honking continues]

132
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:23,336
-[Soryong] Roll up the windows.
-[Giho] The windows, get the windows.

133
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:30,218
[car engine stops]

134
00:08:37,642 --> 00:08:38,685
[Han Do] Is there a problem, sir?

135
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:39,853
[head guard] I should be asking you that.

136
00:08:40,603 --> 00:08:42,355
You're trespassing on private property.

137
00:08:42,439 --> 00:08:43,440
Private property?

138
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:44,858
-Oh!
-Oh, it is?

139
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:46,901
So this place belongs to…

140
00:08:47,777 --> 00:08:49,988
Huh. We didn't know. We had no idea.

141
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:52,782
We didn't mean to stop here, actually.

142
00:08:53,742 --> 00:08:56,286
Uh… my wife's feeling
a little carsick or something,

143
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:58,705
so we were taking a break for her.

144
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:01,249
-[whispers] We're taking a break…
-[gags, groans]

145
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,835
-How are you, sweetie?
-Not good.

146
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:05,754
-[Han Do] Oh my, she's not doing too well.
-Uh…

147
00:09:06,504 --> 00:09:07,589
Think you're pregnant?

148
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:10,258
-[Giho] Uh…
-You think your sister's pregnant?

149
00:09:10,341 --> 00:09:11,926
-Get going.
-Yep, we're leaving, sir.

150
00:09:12,010 --> 00:09:13,261
-We're sorry. We're so sorry, yup.
-Hurry it up.

151
00:09:13,344 --> 00:09:15,597
-[whispers] What the…
-[Giho] You suck at acting. My sister?

152
00:09:15,680 --> 00:09:17,015
[Giho] You seriously thought
that would work?

153
00:09:17,098 --> 00:09:18,266
[Han Do] What should I have said,
she's your daughter?

154
00:09:18,349 --> 00:09:20,185
-No! That would've been even weirder!
-[Han Do] What was I suppo--

155
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:21,519
-[knocking]
-[Soryong] The doors. Lock the doors.

156
00:09:21,603 --> 00:09:22,812
I need you to let me inspect your vehicle.

157
00:09:22,896 --> 00:09:24,272
-[Soryong] Lock it. Lock it.
-Please open the door.

158
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:26,107
-[Giho] Lock it.
-Drive away. Drive away.

159
00:09:26,191 --> 00:09:27,817
-[head guard] Please open the door, sir.
-[Soryong] Go. Just go. Just drive!

160
00:09:27,901 --> 00:09:29,527
[head guard] Stop! Open this door! Hey!

161
00:09:29,611 --> 00:09:32,155
[guards shouting indistinctly]

162
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:35,992
[head guard] Stop them!
They've got something!

163
00:09:36,076 --> 00:09:37,243
-Don't let them get away!
-Back up, back up!

164
00:09:39,579 --> 00:09:40,747
Back up. Whoa, whoa, whoa!

165
00:09:41,331 --> 00:09:44,542
-[Giho] What do we do? No, back up!
-Water's behind us. Back up where?

166
00:09:44,626 --> 00:09:45,919
-Just back up a little more!
-We can't! We gotta go around!

167
00:09:46,002 --> 00:09:47,087
[Giho] Just do it! Go back!

168
00:09:47,796 --> 00:09:50,507
-[guards shouting indistinctly]
-[head guard] Hey! You can't be here!

169
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:51,841
-Water! Water!
-I know! I can't go back any farther!

170
00:09:52,801 --> 00:09:54,552
[♪ intense music playing]

171
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:56,346
-Sir, open up!
-[Giho] Damn it, are you serious?

172
00:09:56,429 --> 00:09:57,680
-[knocking on car]
-[head guard] Open the door, now!

173
00:09:57,764 --> 00:09:59,099
-Ah, dude! Just…
-[guard 1] Sir!

174
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:00,183
-[head guard] Open the door!
-[guard 2] Get out of there.

175
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:01,684
-[rapid knocking]
-[head guard] Open the door. Hurry up!

176
00:10:01,768 --> 00:10:03,728
[guard 2] Jeez!
What is wrong with you people?

177
00:10:04,646 --> 00:10:05,980
Do you have a warrant?

178
00:10:06,064 --> 00:10:08,149
-What warrant?
-You did this all without a warrant.

179
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:10,193
You scared the crap out of us, sir!

180
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:13,488
Your loss.

181
00:10:15,115 --> 00:10:16,491
Because we have our own.

182
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:19,244
[police siren blaring]

183
00:10:20,829 --> 00:10:23,706
God, we've been driving around in circles
getting away from these thugs.

184
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,208
-What took you so long?
-[Detective Yu] Calm down, we're here.

185
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,793
You see me? Over here.

186
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:29,671
[Detective Yu]
Tell them Major Crimes is taking over.

187
00:10:29,754 --> 00:10:31,965
Keep clear. This is an active crime scene!

188
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:36,511
[operator] Another one coming up.
Whoa, slow down, easy.

189
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:39,180
[crew worker 1] Lower it.
Good, good. Keep it steady.

190
00:10:39,264 --> 00:10:40,765
[crew worker 2] Slowly, slowly.

191
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:41,850
[crew worker 1] Set it down there.

192
00:10:42,934 --> 00:10:44,102
[crew worker 3]
How much more do we have?

193
00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:45,728
-[crew worker 1] We've got a lot more.
-[crew worker 3] We keep at it then.

194
00:10:45,812 --> 00:10:47,147
[Detective Yu]
Call for backup if you need.

195
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:49,190
Be thorough. Make sure you get everything.

196
00:10:49,274 --> 00:10:50,984
[crew worker 1] Understood, sir.

197
00:10:51,067 --> 00:10:52,068
[operator] Left. Left!

198
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:54,404
[crew worker on radio]
A search is currently underway.

199
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:55,697
Repeat, search underway.

200
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,657
[crew worker] Go right, slow down.

201
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:00,869
[Detective Yu]
Make sure to wrap those tight!

202
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,538
[crew worker 1] Whoa, careful. Careful.

203
00:11:04,122 --> 00:11:06,541
[Detective Yu] You break even one of them
and it's your ass!

204
00:11:08,418 --> 00:11:10,628
I can't even… How many are there?

205
00:11:10,712 --> 00:11:12,755
How long were all those bodies down there?

206
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:15,508
[Giho] I don'-- I don't get how someone
could do something so horrible.

207
00:11:15,592 --> 00:11:16,885
They're psychopaths.

208
00:11:16,968 --> 00:11:18,553
All right, keep your eyes peeled!

209
00:11:18,636 --> 00:11:19,637
[crew worker 1] Will do, sir.

210
00:11:20,805 --> 00:11:24,559
So, time to find this Hanju guy
and take him into custody. Okay?

211
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:25,685
[Detective Yu] Hey, rookie!

212
00:11:25,768 --> 00:11:26,978
[rookie] Yes, sir.

213
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:29,105
[sighs]

214
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:35,028
[police sirens blaring]

215
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:37,197
[♪ ominous music playing]

216
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:43,620
[detective] We came with a warrant
for search and seizure.

217
00:11:43,703 --> 00:11:45,622
You think you can block us, huh?

218
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:46,831
Get out of our way!

219
00:11:46,915 --> 00:11:47,916
[Detective Yu] Let me.

220
00:11:47,999 --> 00:11:49,000
All right.

221
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:51,669
You folks need to stop this obstruction.

222
00:11:51,753 --> 00:11:52,754
Step aside.

223
00:11:54,923 --> 00:11:56,424
[♪ tense music playing]

224
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:11,189
What's this about, huh?

225
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:14,317
We recovered several dead bodies
from a reservoir on your property.

226
00:12:15,443 --> 00:12:17,612
You're gonna have to come
with us, Mr. Cho.

227
00:12:17,695 --> 00:12:19,030
You're wanted for questioning.

228
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:23,159
Do you have any idea who I am?

229
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:25,036
-Mr. Cho Jinman.
-Not what I meant.

230
00:12:27,247 --> 00:12:30,458
I cannot be arrested
as a member of the National Assembly.

231
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:32,669
That is my privilege and I'll be using it.

232
00:12:33,711 --> 00:12:34,921
[Jinman] Article 44.

233
00:12:35,505 --> 00:12:37,674
"No member of the Assembly
shall be arrested or detained

234
00:12:37,757 --> 00:12:39,842
without the consent of the Assembly."

235
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:43,680
Questioning, huh? [chuckles]

236
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:47,141
Well, why don't you come back
with an Assembly-approved warrant?

237
00:12:47,225 --> 00:12:49,811
Assemblyman,
the privilege you're referring to

238
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:52,438
technically applies
only when Assembly's in session.

239
00:12:52,522 --> 00:12:54,065
The session doesn't start until September.

240
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:55,817
It seems you aren't aware
that a special session

241
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:58,152
is set to convene on this very day.

242
00:13:01,364 --> 00:13:05,535
So if you'd like to arrest me,
I suggest you follow the proper protocol

243
00:13:06,077 --> 00:13:09,455
and request a warrant for arrest
that's approved by my peers.

244
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:14,085
I doubt these findings will be reported
to parliament until tomorrow.

245
00:13:14,168 --> 00:13:16,921
The media is gonna catch wind of this,
and once that happens…

246
00:13:18,047 --> 00:13:19,757
it's a matter of time
before that warrant's out.

247
00:13:21,301 --> 00:13:22,885
[chuckles] Sorry.

248
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:26,347
I'm afraid getting that approval
won't be as easy as you think.

249
00:13:26,431 --> 00:13:28,599
