You don't want it then.

507
00:28:47,643 --> 00:28:48,769
What are they?

508
00:28:49,770 --> 00:28:51,521
-Your terms.
-You learn pretty quick.

509
00:28:51,605 --> 00:28:53,106
I've always liked you, you know.

510
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:56,151
I'll try to get to the point then,
so you can get to it.

511
00:28:56,944 --> 00:28:57,945
Yeah, please do.

512
00:29:04,284 --> 00:29:05,744
I'll make a confession.

513
00:29:07,746 --> 00:29:09,957
Without the president
falling on his sword,

514
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:11,500
it won't be a good ending.

515
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,336
Added bonus is he ties in to the story.

516
00:29:15,462 --> 00:29:16,630
So interview me.

517
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:18,131
[sighs]

518
00:29:18,966 --> 00:29:20,384
Are you really confessing?

519
00:29:22,386 --> 00:29:23,637
Or are you just…

520
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:25,973
indulging yourself?

521
00:29:27,641 --> 00:29:30,102
When we were preparing
the episode in secret,

522
00:29:30,727 --> 00:29:32,980
I had every intention
of going up against them.

523
00:29:33,563 --> 00:29:34,815
[President Koo] But then…

524
00:29:34,898 --> 00:29:36,817
the detective who was
investigating the case,

525
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:38,902
and had procured key evidence,
turned up dead.

526
00:29:41,279 --> 00:29:43,532
I thought I'd be next on the kill list.

527
00:29:44,950 --> 00:29:46,493
Tell me you wouldn't stand down.

528
00:29:47,953 --> 00:29:49,579
I would've aired the episode,

529
00:29:49,663 --> 00:29:50,956
no matter what.

530
00:29:52,874 --> 00:29:54,001
Ah.

531
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,087
Fearless people such as yourself

532
00:29:57,587 --> 00:29:59,089
might not be able to understand.

533
00:29:59,756 --> 00:30:01,800
I didn't have the stomach to go all in.

534
00:30:02,801 --> 00:30:03,802
I am…

535
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:08,849
I am but an ordinary man.

536
00:30:09,891 --> 00:30:11,226
[♪ pensive music playing]

537
00:30:19,568 --> 00:30:21,570
We make decisions
every second of our lives.

538
00:30:23,196 --> 00:30:24,740
We do what we think is right,

539
00:30:26,783 --> 00:30:28,785
regardless of any consequences.

540
00:30:39,337 --> 00:30:41,214
You wanna let him redeem himself?

541
00:30:44,342 --> 00:30:47,929
You wanna put this blatant attempt
at whitewashing his name on our show?

542
00:30:48,013 --> 00:30:49,389
It's the only option we have right now--

543
00:30:49,473 --> 00:30:50,474
[Han Do] No.

544
00:30:51,099 --> 00:30:52,100
That's not true.

545
00:30:54,269 --> 00:30:56,188
My dad died investigating Hanju.

546
00:30:57,147 --> 00:30:58,440
[Han Do]
Hanju is not the only villain here.

547
00:30:58,523 --> 00:31:01,068
Everyone involved,
from detectives who hid evidence,

548
00:31:01,151 --> 00:31:03,904
and to President Koo,
they're all complicit in this.

549
00:31:04,404 --> 00:31:07,991
You're saying that giving the mic to them
is the only choice we have right now?

550
00:31:08,617 --> 00:31:10,702
-You're being irrational, Mr. Han.
-[scoffs]

551
00:31:10,786 --> 00:31:12,621
[Soryong] Have you forgotten
the reason we're airing this?

552
00:31:12,704 --> 00:31:14,873
The truth behind
the death of Cha Seongwook.

553
00:31:14,956 --> 00:31:16,083
The death of your father,

554
00:31:16,792 --> 00:31:18,460
covered up by the Hanju Group.

555
00:31:19,002 --> 00:31:20,962
Generations of murder and abuse.

556
00:31:21,046 --> 00:31:23,548
Our moral duty
is to show the world this episode.

557
00:31:24,049 --> 00:31:26,426
President Koo's excuses
may very well have an impact on--

558
00:31:26,510 --> 00:31:29,304
That bastard President Koo
was Cho Jinman's accomplice!

559
00:31:29,387 --> 00:31:31,848
And I'll destroy him
by revealing who he is.

560
00:31:32,808 --> 00:31:35,435
I don't wanna air his pathetic sob story
on our show.

561
00:31:35,519 --> 00:31:38,980
I refuse to let him sugarcoat his crimes
so he can be brought down gently.

562
00:31:39,064 --> 00:31:40,148
And the tape?

563
00:31:40,690 --> 00:31:43,026
Cho Haewon's interview. We throw it out?

564
00:31:43,860 --> 00:31:46,071
Are you suggesting
we toss out all our findings,

565
00:31:46,154 --> 00:31:48,156
all the work we've done?
That's what you want?

566
00:31:50,075 --> 00:31:51,326
[Daeyong] We need this for the ratings.

567
00:31:53,328 --> 00:31:55,997
You know, the guy did say he'd resign.

568
00:31:56,748 --> 00:31:59,835
And his apology will help clear
Trigger's name so we can cover this story.

569
00:31:59,918 --> 00:32:01,586
Okay, but that's not even the issue.

570
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:04,798
President Koo could easily stop us
from airing the episode.

571
00:32:04,881 --> 00:32:08,593
I think, before anything,
we should be getting the episode out.

572
00:32:08,677 --> 00:32:10,512
You all know I've tried that approach.

573
00:32:11,304 --> 00:32:14,182
Even the most noble goal,
when achieved through unjust means,

574
00:32:15,267 --> 00:32:16,643
becomes unjust as a whole.

575
00:32:17,227 --> 00:32:19,354
-[deep inhale]
-[deep exhale]

576
00:32:19,437 --> 00:32:20,438
Do.

577
00:32:22,524 --> 00:32:25,861
I'll admit, If I were in his shoes,

578
00:32:26,444 --> 00:32:27,737
I might have done the same thing.

579
00:32:27,821 --> 00:32:28,822
[Giho] Remember when…

580
00:32:30,323 --> 00:32:32,951
when I killed that interview
in exchange for being made full-time?

581
00:32:33,034 --> 00:32:34,161
[sighs]

582
00:32:34,244 --> 00:32:36,079
[Giho] I did everything
the higher-ups asked.

583
00:32:36,163 --> 00:32:37,497
I mean, it's not like
there were death threats.

584
00:32:37,998 --> 00:32:40,375
I just had a chance
to take an opportunity.

585
00:32:42,335 --> 00:32:44,129
So maybe what President Koo
did back then wasn't so--

586
00:32:44,212 --> 00:32:46,798
This is exactly
what President Koo wants us to do.

587
00:32:47,924 --> 00:32:50,218
He wants to guilt-trip all of us

588
00:32:50,719 --> 00:32:54,139
to make us sympathize
with his cowardly, self-serving decisions.

589
00:32:58,351 --> 00:32:59,352
Then sit this out.

590
00:33:02,898 --> 00:33:03,982
All or nothing…

591
00:33:06,193 --> 00:33:07,819
is not an attitude
that works for this show.

592
00:33:09,029 --> 00:33:12,115
Personal qualms,
based on our individual convictions,

593
00:33:12,199 --> 00:33:13,867
have no place in a show like ours.

594
00:33:14,492 --> 00:33:17,787
You must be willing to accept decisions,
even if you disagree,

595
00:33:17,871 --> 00:33:20,624
provided that they're based on fact
and reveal the greater truth.

596
00:33:21,124 --> 00:33:22,667
That's necessary to work here.

597
00:33:23,335 --> 00:33:26,588
It's our moral obligation,
as journalists and producers.

598
00:33:26,671 --> 00:33:28,548
If you put your convictions first then,

599
00:33:31,259 --> 00:33:32,302
I'm afraid to say it,

600
00:33:34,721 --> 00:33:36,181
but your time spent on Trigger

601
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:40,352
was a waste, Mr. Han.

602
00:33:44,064 --> 00:33:45,148
[shaky breath]

603
00:33:48,151 --> 00:33:49,152
[gasps]

604
00:33:49,236 --> 00:33:50,987
Ms. Oh, wait, why… why would you…

605
00:33:51,071 --> 00:33:52,405
-[Giho] Wait. Wait, Do.
-Mister… Mr. Han.

606
00:33:53,073 --> 00:33:54,074
[Daeyong] Mr. Han.

607
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:00,288
[sighs] Come on, Ms. Oh.

608
00:34:00,372 --> 00:34:02,332
What are y'all doing?
Let's make this happen.

609
00:34:15,470 --> 00:34:16,554
[soft sigh]

610
00:34:16,638 --> 00:34:18,640
[♪ gentle music playing]

611
00:34:21,226 --> 00:34:22,477
EP890: Cha Seongwook…

612
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:23,728
Cho Haewon solo interview

613
00:34:31,611 --> 00:34:33,697
-Let's go over that again. First part.
-Right.

614
00:34:33,780 --> 00:34:35,532
Remember that smile you trimmed earlier?

615
00:34:36,116 --> 00:34:37,701
Use that, slow it down, but subtle.

616
00:34:37,784 --> 00:34:39,119
Wait. Okay, stop.

617
00:34:39,786 --> 00:34:42,122
-Should I go get more?
-[Giho] Oh, yes, please.

618
00:34:43,081 --> 00:34:45,667
-[Jiyun] Oh, you're here.
-Which story are you on again?

619
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:47,627
A star producer abusing his workers.

620
00:34:48,253 --> 00:34:50,338
He's a big earner,
so they wanna flush the whole thing.

621
00:34:50,422 --> 00:34:51,798
Pissing away a great story.

622
00:34:52,465 --> 00:34:53,675
Hmm…

623
00:34:53,758 --> 00:34:55,635
I'll bet Ms. Oh would've made it work.

624
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:56,970
True.

625
00:34:57,053 --> 00:34:58,221
"The Confession"

626
00:35:02,434 --> 00:35:03,560
What's wrong?

627
00:35:05,562 --> 00:35:07,105
I can't write a single line.

628
00:35:08,064 --> 00:35:10,567
I think this case
is just too big for me. [sighs]

629
00:35:11,359 --> 00:35:13,903
I really, really want this
to be a groundbreaking episode.

630
00:35:16,031 --> 00:35:17,240
But I just can't.

631
00:35:19,909 --> 00:35:21,536
From time to time, people ask me,

632
00:35:22,078 --> 00:35:25,582
"No teleprompter,
so how do you memorize all those lines?"

633
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:29,836
Trigger scripts
aren't just words on a screen.

634
00:35:31,087 --> 00:35:32,422
Instead, I just…

635
00:35:33,381 --> 00:35:34,966
I close my eyes, and I listen.

636
00:35:35,675 --> 00:35:36,885
I think about…

637
00:35:37,552 --> 00:35:41,222
the stories, and the heartbreak,
the poor victims.

638
00:35:41,306 --> 00:35:43,725
[mimics a projector]
A projector starts rolling in my head.

639
00:35:45,769 --> 00:35:47,312
And the words just flow out of me.

640
00:35:48,188 --> 00:35:49,314
And you wanna know why?

641
00:35:51,274 --> 00:35:53,485
It's because Ms. Hong, when she wrote,

642
00:35:54,819 --> 00:35:56,446
she poured her heart out.

643
00:35:59,741 --> 00:36:01,910
She would always say,
"Before you deliver your lines,

644
00:36:01,993 --> 00:36:05,330
try to read not the words,
but the emotions."

645
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:10,043
[phone buzzing]

646
00:36:10,752 --> 00:36:11,753
Hong Nahee

647
00:36:11,836 --> 00:36:13,088
[chuckles]

648
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:14,881
Yes, Ms. Hong.

649
00:36:16,466 --> 00:36:17,467
[muttering] The emotions…

650
00:36:21,471 --> 00:36:22,681
KP…

651
00:36:27,227 --> 00:36:28,311
[Giho] KP…

652
00:36:40,031 --> 00:36:42,117
[♪ gentle music playing]

653
00:36:58,550 --> 00:37:00,677
[Soryong] I'm heading over for
the final interview with President Koo.

654
00:37:02,178 --> 00:37:03,388
If any of you wanna join,

655
00:37:04,472 --> 00:37:05,598
feel free to come.

656
00:37:12,355 --> 00:37:13,815
Okay.

657
00:37:25,618 --> 00:37:27,036
This is quite the audience you've brought.

658
00:37:34,586 --> 00:37:36,129
[camera beeping]

659
00:37:38,590 --> 00:37:39,758
It's all set. We can begin now.

660
00:37:41,593 --> 00:37:45,638
The media has an obligation
to serve the nation's citizens

661
00:37:45,722 --> 00:37:47,056
by putting checks on those in power

662
00:37:47,140 --> 00:37:49,976
through fair, balanced,
and truthful reporting.

663
00:37:50,852 --> 00:37:51,853
But regretfully,

664
00:37:52,604 --> 00:37:55,148
when faced with
the imposing authority of Hanju,

665
00:37:55,732 --> 00:37:58,026
I failed to uphold these fundamentals.

666
00:37:58,109 --> 00:38:00,403
Back then, everyone reporting on the story

667
00:38:00,487 --> 00:38:02,572
was either demoted
or fired from their job.

668
00:38:03,072 --> 00:38:04,866
[high-pitched ringing]

669
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:08,870
You know,
controlling your facial expressions

670
00:38:08,953 --> 00:38:10,371
is part of your job description.

671
00:38:10,955 --> 00:38:12,207
God, you people…

672
00:38:12,290 --> 00:38:14,083
It wouldn't kill you
to lighten up once in a while.

673
00:38:16,085 --> 00:38:17,420
It sounds like…

674
00:38:18,755 --> 00:38:21,841
even after our interview,
you feel no remorse.

675
00:38:22,842 --> 00:38:24,219
[inhales deeply]

676
00:38:28,389 --> 00:38:29,724
[pops]

677
00:38:29,808 --> 00:38:32,310
Remorse isn't an emotion I find useful.

678
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:35,396
Although I felt sentimental
towards the end of that.

679
00:38:36,981 --> 00:38:40,109
It was as though you finished writing
a letter I'd left incomplete.

680
00:38:47,283 --> 00:38:48,618
[door opens]

681
00:38:48,701 --> 00:38:50,453
-[door closes]
-All right, let's hurry.

682
00:38:50,537 --> 00:38:53,873
We're gonna splice in this interview
right after the interview with Cho Haewon.

683
00:38:53,957 --> 00:38:55,166
Let's go!

684
00:38:58,419 --> 00:39:01,339
[President Koo laughs]
The look on Soryong's face was priceless.

685
00:39:01,422 --> 00:39:03,216
[Huiwon] I'll keep an eye on
the Master Control Room

686
00:39:03,299 --> 00:39:05,677
to make sure
the episode doesn't go off the rails.

687
00:39:11,850 --> 00:39:14,018
You do that. I'll watch from my office.

688
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:15,353
Yes, sir.

689
00:39:18,690 --> 00:39:19,774
[Jiyun] Let's just leave it here and…

690
00:39:19,858 --> 00:39:21,317
[worker] Cut down that glare a little bit.

691
00:39:21,401 --> 00:39:22,861
-[Jiyun] Placement's okay?
-[Giho] Other way. Other way.

692
00:39:22,944 --> 00:39:23,945
-Other…
-Yes.

693
00:39:24,028 --> 00:39:25,321
Like this, huh?

694
00:39:25,947 --> 00:39:27,198
"Cha Seongwook Disappearance Case
Producer Koo Hyeongtae"

695
00:39:27,282 --> 00:39:28,533
-[Jiyun] Let's do it like that.
-[Giho] Yeah, looks good.

696
00:39:31,661 --> 00:39:33,329
[♪ brisk music playing]

697
00:39:40,420 --> 00:39:42,005
The writers eat this stuff?
That explains--

698
00:39:42,088 --> 00:39:43,381
-It's starting, it's starting now!
-[Jeongseok] Oh.

699
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:56,019
"The Confession"

700
00:39:57,395 --> 00:40:01,065
20 years ago, a young television star
just hitting his stride,

701
00:40:01,149 --> 00:40:02,317
suddenly went missing.

702
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,860
Disappearing without a trace.

703
00:40:06,029 --> 00:40:08,323
I just wanna know where my son is.

704
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:09,908
[Soryong] The "January Man" statue,

705
00:40:09,991 --> 00:40:12,702
kept for years
in the lobby of Hanju's offices,

706
00:40:12,785 --> 00:40:16,205
was confirmed to contain
the bronze-encased head of Mr. Cha.

707
00:40:16,289 --> 00:40:18,291
It was determined that Ms. Cho Haewon,

708
00:40:18,374 --> 00:40:21,169
the oldest daughter
of the powerful Hanju Group family…

709
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:22,921
and his lover…

710
00:40:23,671 --> 00:40:24,672
was the murderer.

711
00:40:25,465 --> 00:40:29,761
And now,
the unspeakable crimes of the Hanju family

712
00:40:29,844 --> 00:40:31,846
have finally come to the surface.

713
00:40:32,722 --> 00:40:35,183
However, as part of this broadcast,

714
00:40:35,266 --> 00:40:38,937
a past omission will be addressed by us.

715
00:40:41,022 --> 00:40:43,191
What you see here is a 20-year-old tape,

716
00:40:43,816 --> 00:40:47,528
Trigger Episode 890, completely unaired,

717
00:40:47,612 --> 00:40:51,407
containing the full details
of the Cha Seongwook murder investigation.

718
00:40:51,991 --> 00:40:53,034
However, this tape

719
00:40:53,826 --> 00:40:58,539
was hidden away by none other than
a member of the Trigger production staff.

720
00:40:59,207 --> 00:41:03,419
So, today's episode will contain
both a confession and an apology,

721
00:41:03,503 --> 00:41:06,547
for Trigger's actions
and our shameful past.

722
00:41:13,763 --> 00:41:15,181
I wanted to possess him.

723
00:41:15,264 --> 00:41:20,144
"Cho Haewon, 24 years old"

724
00:41:20,228 --> 00:41:22,188
I wanted to keep him forever.

725
00:41:23,690 --> 00:41:24,691
Are you the one…

726
00:41:25,775 --> 00:41:27,110
who killed Cha Seongwook?

727
00:41:28,111 --> 00:41:30,279
[♪ tense music playing]

728
00:41:30,780 --> 00:41:31,781
Yes.

729
00:41:35,034 --> 00:41:36,160
Why did you do it?

730
00:41:38,121 --> 00:41:39,247
That face…

731
00:41:43,042 --> 00:41:44,210
that face of his.

732
00:41:49,674 --> 00:41:51,634
My father wanted to punish me,

733
00:41:54,012 --> 00:41:55,179
so he stole it.

734
00:41:57,140 --> 00:41:58,808
[Soryong] The producer in the footage

735
00:41:58,891 --> 00:42:02,020
is the sitting president of KNS,
Mr. Koo Hyeongtae.

736
00:42:02,603 --> 00:42:04,647
He wishes to make a confession

737
00:42:05,148 --> 00:42:07,358
and issue an apology to our viewers.

738
00:42:08,693 --> 00:42:10,361
Back then, everyone reporting on the story

739
00:42:10,445 --> 00:42:12,822
was either demoted
or fired from their job.

740
00:42:13,573 --> 00:42:15,867
In certain cases,
their lives were threatened.

741
00:42:17,910 --> 00:42:19,495
So I abandoned the story.

742
00:42:20,371 --> 00:42:21,622
"Please help find my son Cha Seongwook"

743
00:42:21,706 --> 00:42:23,041
[President Koo] 20 years went by…

744
00:42:24,042 --> 00:42:27,962
I tried to relieve myself of guilt
by justifying my actions.

745
00:42:28,046 --> 00:42:29,297
I told myself…

746
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:32,925
that I was fulfilling my duties
as a journalist by staying alive,

747
00:42:33,926 --> 00:42:35,261
to fight another day.

748
00:42:38,181 --> 00:42:39,515
However, I now believe…

749
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:45,772
the time has come for me to give in
and stop deluding myself.

750
00:42:46,355 --> 00:42:49,442
On my honor as a journalist,
this is a confession

751
00:42:50,026 --> 00:42:51,569
and my final interview.

752
00:42:53,446 --> 00:42:55,907
I assume responsibility for my actions,

753
00:42:56,616 --> 00:42:57,867
and therefore…

754
00:42:58,826 --> 00:43:01,496
I will resign as the KNS president.

755
00:43:08,586 --> 00:43:10,004
We, the staff of Trigger,

756
00:43:10,088 --> 00:43:11,839
take this opportunity to remind ourselves

757
00:43:11,923 --> 00:43:13,758
of a past lapse
in our journalistic integrity.

758
00:43:14,550 --> 00:43:16,803
To our viewers, our fellow citizens,

759
00:43:16,886 --> 00:43:19,514
we humbly and sincerely apologize.

760
00:43:24,352 --> 00:43:27,563
Trigger vows to give this case
