[♪ gentle music playing]

1001
00:55:05,552 --> 00:55:07,930
[Han Do] I guess, after working
for the network for some time,

1002
00:55:09,056 --> 00:55:11,058
I came to hold Trigger
to a higher standard,

1003
00:55:11,141 --> 00:55:12,351
and I expected better from them.

1004
00:55:12,935 --> 00:55:14,269
[Sangmok] Please just give me more time.

1005
00:55:14,353 --> 00:55:17,189
I'll tell my wife I'm divorcing her.
I'll do it today, please!

1006
00:55:17,940 --> 00:55:19,233
Please, just give me a little…

1007
00:55:19,733 --> 00:55:21,652
[sighs] Damn it.

1008
00:55:21,735 --> 00:55:23,403
-[door closes]
-[Sangmok] Damn it.

1009
00:55:23,987 --> 00:55:25,405
Damn it! Shit!

1010
00:55:28,492 --> 00:55:30,619
"Lee Sangmok, Trigger"

1011
00:55:36,458 --> 00:55:38,293
[Han Do]
And I couldn't accept that you guys,

1012
00:55:38,377 --> 00:55:40,170
of all people, had let me down.

1013
00:55:40,254 --> 00:55:41,838
"KNS moved to a new building!"

1014
00:55:47,344 --> 00:55:48,512
Okay, so?

1015
00:55:50,097 --> 00:55:51,181
Who was the other woman then?

1016
00:55:53,850 --> 00:55:54,851
You wanna know?

1017
00:55:58,021 --> 00:55:59,940
[sighs] I guess not.

1018
00:56:00,566 --> 00:56:02,609
[deep breath]

1019
00:56:06,071 --> 00:56:07,906
Mind if I also ask you a question?

1020
00:56:09,992 --> 00:56:12,119
Why do you exclusively date
total scumbags?

1021
00:56:13,036 --> 00:56:16,415
[laughs]

1022
00:56:17,624 --> 00:56:19,376
[Soryong] Uh… [chuckles]

1023
00:56:21,003 --> 00:56:22,838
[sighs] I guess…

1024
00:56:26,174 --> 00:56:27,593
with men who…

1025
00:56:27,676 --> 00:56:29,303
claim to like me, I don't turn them down.

1026
00:56:29,386 --> 00:56:30,387
[scoffs]

1027
00:56:30,470 --> 00:56:31,722
I don't know.

1028
00:56:33,098 --> 00:56:34,933
I suppose I just say, "Why not?"

1029
00:56:35,559 --> 00:56:37,102
Someone opens their heart…

1030
00:56:38,562 --> 00:56:39,771
you don't turn them down?

1031
00:56:41,023 --> 00:56:43,025
[♪ gentle music playing]

1032
00:56:44,109 --> 00:56:46,320
Whoa, what are you doing?

1033
00:56:48,363 --> 00:56:49,781
Let's try the other way around.

1034
00:56:50,741 --> 00:56:52,409
Tell someone you like him first.

1035
00:56:55,037 --> 00:56:57,539
[Han Do] Wouldn't be the first time
you came at someone without warning.

1036
00:56:58,749 --> 00:57:00,042
And if you did, well…

1037
00:57:03,587 --> 00:57:05,088
I might start trusting again.

1038
00:57:24,691 --> 00:57:25,901
[Soryong] Oh, Detective Yu.

1039
00:57:28,278 --> 00:57:29,321
You two dating?

1040
00:57:29,404 --> 00:57:30,822
No. No way.

1041
00:57:32,449 --> 00:57:33,533
Is something wrong?

1042
00:57:36,328 --> 00:57:38,330
[♪ ominous sting]

1043
00:57:41,667 --> 00:57:44,753
[Giho] So this was discovered
at Cho Jinman's house?

1044
00:57:45,337 --> 00:57:46,797
An anonymous trust or something?

1045
00:57:49,091 --> 00:57:50,550
Something smelled fishy,

1046
00:57:51,134 --> 00:57:52,135
so I did some digging.

1047
00:57:52,719 --> 00:57:53,720
[Detective Yu] And it turns out

1048
00:57:54,388 --> 00:57:57,933
an enormous sum of money from Hanju
went into this account.

1049
00:57:58,767 --> 00:58:00,477
-When did this happen?
-[Detective Yu] Exactly.

1050
00:58:01,061 --> 00:58:02,229
The date's what matters here.

1051
00:58:03,021 --> 00:58:04,022
It was deposited

1052
00:58:04,523 --> 00:58:05,816
the day before Cho Haewon's death.

1053
00:58:05,899 --> 00:58:08,902
[♪ intriguing music playing]

1054
00:58:11,863 --> 00:58:14,408
The autopsy… never happened.

1055
00:58:16,660 --> 00:58:17,911
[sharp exhale]

1056
00:58:19,162 --> 00:58:20,288
Does that mean…

1057
00:58:26,420 --> 00:58:27,671
Cho Haewon…

1058
00:58:28,964 --> 00:58:30,090
is still alive.

1059
00:58:31,717 --> 00:58:34,761
[♪ intriguing music continues]

1060
00:59:03,623 --> 00:59:05,834
[♪ closing theme music playing]
